{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2fece769-7dda-4446-b7d8-2fbbdea02c8b","content":"Let me check the latest xUnit v3 package version and then implement the migration.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01HiK7yAbCAH7wHzLZrQuCRB","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://api.nuget.org/v3-flatcontainer/xunit.v3/index.json"},"type":"function","toolTitle":"Fetching web content","intentionSummary":"https://api.nuget.org/v3-flatcontainer/xunit.v3/index.json"}],"interactionId":"3b9aeaa7-b7cd-46c6-8ee0-93441af29dee","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I understand the project. Let me plan the migration from xUnit.net v2 to v3:\n\n1. **`TestProject.csproj`**: \n   - Replace `xunit` 2.9.3 with `xunit.v3` (latest stable)\n   - Replace `xunit.runner.visualstudio` 2.8.2 with `xunit.runner.visualstudio` v3 or remove it (in v3, the runner is built into the test assembly)\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — v3 doesn't need it for running, but for VS Test Explorer integration it might still be needed. Actually, in xUnit v3, tests are self-hosting executables. The project SDK changes from `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` to `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` but with `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>`. Wait, let me think about this more carefully.\n   \n   In v3, I need `xunit.v3` as the main package, and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` is still required for `dotnet test` integration. The `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package in v3 handles the VS Test Explorer integration, so I should update that to v3 as well rather than removing it.\n\nFor the test project structure, v3 tests are self-executable, so I need to set `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` in the project file.\n\nThe `[TestCaseOrderer]` attribute syntax has changed in v3 — it now uses a single-type generic version instead of the two-string constructor that v2 used.\n\nSimilarly, the `[assembly: CollectionBehavior]` attribute now takes a `typeof()` parameter instead of string-based type and assembly names.\n\nFor `global.json`, the test runner configuration might need adjustment, though `dotnet test` should continue to work with v3. me now implement the changes. For xUnit v3, I need to switch to the `xunit.v3` meta-package which includes everything, removing the separate SDK and runner packages. The project also needs `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` since v3 tests compile to executables. The namespace stays as `Xunit`, though some types moved to `Xunit.v3`. I'm also checking how attributes like `TestCaseOrderer` changed — v3 uses a Type parameter instead of string names.\n\nFor `CollectionBehavior`, v3 switched from string-based type and assembly names to using `typeof()` directly. Now I need to look up the exact version number for the stable xUnit v3 release to make sure I'm using the right package version. I'm wondering if xunit.v3 comes with its own test runner built in, or if I need to add the VSTest adapter separately for `dotnet test` to work properly. Let me just try the migration and see what the build tells me.","outputTokens":1806,"requestId":"8050:106126:76DC3E:7E27F2:6A044D51"},"id":"01ce075b-6b31-4b4c-8819-c72527013116","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:07:50.493Z","parentId":"7322b8b1-2977-434d-9db0-dc372898af46"}
